<p class="">I think there is a little confusion here. The Clerks at the Table and I have to go on what Ministers say as to their responsibility. It is not a matter which I or the Table can judge. Ministers have said that anything that Field Marshal Lord Montgomery has said as a servant of N.A.T.O. is not a matter for which Ministers are responsible. The Clerks at the Table are entitled—indeed it is their duty—to assume that the fact is so. Beyond that, I am afraid I cannot assist the hon. Gentleman.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
