            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-0cd128d8-abdb-458a-848a-bce615502fd4">
                Mr. Shinwell
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-0cd128d8-abdb-458a-848a-bce615502fd4" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1954-12-09/debates/3f55a8e0-5b15-4493-a61b-81861207b0bd/FieldMarshalMontgomery(MilitaryDocuments)#contribution-0cd128d8-abdb-458a-848a-bce615502fd4">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">Leaving aside for the moment any question of disrespect to Field Marshal Montgomery, because I am quite sure none is intended—certainly so far as many of us are concerned, we have the highest regard for the Field Marshal, more particularly when he is making desperate efforts to support the Prime Minister—may I ask the right hon. Gentleman whether it is customary, <span id="1112" class="column-number" data-column-number="1112"></span> apart from the Official Secrets Act, which I do not invoke at the present moment, for officers in the Army, of whatever rank, to retain secret documents without the permission of the Prime Minister, and whether the Prime Minister has not a record of those secret documents?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-0cd128d8-abdb-458a-848a-bce615502fd4" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1954-12-09/debates/3f55a8e0-5b15-4493-a61b-81861207b0bd/FieldMarshalMontgomery(MilitaryDocuments)#contribution-0cd128d8-abdb-458a-848a-bce615502fd4">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
